                                "byte_start": 90014,
                                "byte_stop": 125854,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has the opinion of the court this morning in two cases."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.946,
                        "stop": 226.012,
                        "byte_start": 125854,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.946,
                                "stop": 22.655,
                                "byte_start": 125854,
                                "byte_stop": 180711,
                                "text": "First case I have is The Permanent Mission of India, et al. versus The City of New York, 06-0134."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.655,
                                "stop": 30.256,
                                "byte_start": 180711,
                                "byte_stop": 211118,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Courts of Appeals for the Second Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.256,
                                "stop": 48.85,
                                "byte_start": 211118,
                                "byte_stop": 285514,
                                "text": "For several years New York City has levied property taxes against the Permanent Mission of India to the United States and the Mongolian Ministry of Foreign Affairs for the portions of their New York buildings used to house lower level employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.85,
                                "stop": 66.013,
                                "byte_start": 285514,
                                "byte_stop": 354164,
                                "text": "Petitioners have refused to pay those taxes by operation of the New York Law the unpaid taxes converted into tax liens and the City sought a declaration in State Court that the tax liens were valid."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.013,
                                "stop": 78.166,
                                "byte_start": 354164,
                                "byte_stop": 402752,
                                "text": "Petitioners remove to Federal Court and argued that they were immune from the suits under the Foreign Sovereign Immunities Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.166,
                                "stop": 100.4,
                                "byte_start": 402752,
                                "byte_stop": 491673,
                                "text": "The District Court disagreed relying on the acts exception to immunity for \u201cimmovable property\u201d which provides that a foreign state shall not be immune from jurisdiction in any case in which \u201crights and immovable property situated in the United States are in the issue.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.4,
                                "stop": 103.642,
                                "byte_start": 491673,
                                "byte_stop": 504630,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.642,
                                "stop": 109.897,
                                "byte_start": 504630,
                                "byte_stop": 529603,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today, we affirmed the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.897,
                                "stop": 119.025,
                                "byte_start": 529603,
                                "byte_stop": 566174,
                                "text": "We hold that an action seeking a declaration of the validity of a tax lien places rights and immovable property in the issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.025,
                                "stop": 131.887,
                                "byte_start": 566174,
                                "byte_stop": 617583,
                                "text": "Contrary to petitioners\u2019 position, the immovable property exception does not expressly limit itself to cases in which the specific right at issue is titled ownership or possession."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.887,
                                "stop": 137.258,
                                "byte_start": 617583,
                                "byte_stop": 639108,
                                "text": "Rather the exception focuses more broadly on rights in property."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.258,
                                "stop": 148.61,
                                "byte_start": 639108,
                                "byte_stop": 684456,
                                "text": "At the time, of the acts adoption in 1976, Black\u2019s Law Dictionary defined a lien as a charge or security or incumbrance upon property."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.61,
                                "stop": 159.7,
                                "byte_start": 684456,
                                "byte_stop": 728865,
                                "text": "Incumbrance in turn was defined as \u201cany right or interest in land which may subsist in another to the diminution of its value.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.7,
                                "stop": 169.887,
                                "byte_start": 728865,
                                "byte_stop": 769616,
                                "text": "The most recent edition of Black\u2019s similarly defines lien as a \u201clegal right or interest that a creditor has in another\u2019s property.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.887,
                                "stop": 174.988,
                                "byte_start": 769616,
                                "byte_stop": 789991,
                                "text": "The practical effects of a lien are consistent with these definitions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.988,
                                "stop": 181.633,
                                "byte_start": 789991,
                                "byte_stop": 816636,
                                "text": "A lien on real property runs with the land and is enforceable against subsequent purchasers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.633,
                                "stop": 188.941,
                                "byte_start": 816636,
                                "byte_stop": 845789,
                                "text": "As such a lien has an immediate adverse effect upon the amount to which property could be sold."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.941,
                                "stop": 198.623,
                                "byte_start": 845789,
                                "byte_stop": 884554,
                                "text": "This constitutes a direct interference with the property and inhibits one of the quintessential rights property ownership the right to convey."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.623,
                                "stop": 206.346,
                                "byte_start": 884554,
                                "byte_stop": 915483,
                                "text": "It is therefore plain that a suit to establish the validity of a lien implicates rights and immovable property."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.346,
                                "stop": 220.29,
                                "byte_start": 915483,
                                "byte_stop": 971176,
                                "text": "Two well recognized and related purposes of the act adoption of the restrictive view of sovereign immunity and codification of international law at the time of the acts enactment support our reading of the text."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.29,
                                "stop": 226.012,
                                "byte_start": 971176,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion which Justice Breyer has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
